	(221, 1, 'PAMM Accounts: How It Works', 'PAMM Accounts: How It Works', 'PAMM-Accounts-How-It-Works', 'PAMM Accounts: How It Works', 'PAMM Accounts: How It Works', '&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;\n	&lt;strong&gt;PAMM: HOW IT WORK&amp;#39;s&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;\n	Let us assume &lt;strong&gt;Mr. Leo&lt;/strong&gt; prefers to become a Forex Money Manager using Forexray. Once the partnership agreement is signed, Leo and also Forexray proceed to the PAMM setup. A unique referral account opening link will be provided to the Money Manager to attract clients directly into his PAMM. Manager Leo can easily advertise his managed account services through different approaches, including personal promotion, exhibitions, Forex forums and also associated web sites.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;\n	&lt;strong&gt;The Investors Cody, Milo&lt;/strong&gt; and also &lt;strong&gt;Hugo&lt;/strong&gt; are interested in investment systems as well as apply for a managed account with Forexray to be attached to Leo&amp;#39;s PAMM. Once the Limited Power of Attorney (LPOA) is signed and also the client&amp;#39;s primary account deposit has arrived to Forexray, the managed account is connected to Master PAMM account. &lt;strong&gt;Investor Milo &lt;/strong&gt;has decided to invest 4 000 USD while Investor Cody and &lt;strong&gt;Investor Hugo&lt;/strong&gt; go with 3 000 USD each.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;\n	&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.forexray.com/uploads/1400833108_1735517142_fxray.jpg&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;About Forexray&quot; src=&quot;https://www.forexray.com/uploads/1400833108_1735517142_fxray.jpg&quot; style=&quot;width:392; height: 243px;-webkit-border-radius: 4px; -moz-border-radius: 4px; border-radius: 4px;-moz-box-shadow: 0px 12px 11px #8c7c7c;-webkit-box-shadow: 0px 12px 11px #8c7c7c;box-shadow: 0px 12px 11px #8c7c7c;border: 1px solid #c9cdd0;margin-bottom:14px;&quot; title=&quot;About-Forexray&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;\n	Let us assume manager Leo&amp;#39;s performance fee is 30% from the profit he earns for the client. These Operation fee is determined in the LPOA. Manager Leo has gained 2 000 USD on the initial investment of 10 000 USD. These PAMM account balance following the first month has grown to 12 000 USD. The particular profit (2 000 USD) is actually allocated to all of managed accounts dependent on their share of the Master PAMM account balance.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;\n	With the initial investment of 4 000 USD, &lt;strong&gt;Investor Milo&lt;/strong&gt; has gained a profit of 800 USD after the first month (40% of 2 000 USD). 30% of profit earned is matter to Manager Leo&amp;#39;s reward: 240 USD. &lt;strong&gt;Investor Milo&amp;#39;s end balance right after the first month is actually 4 000 USD + 560 (800-240) USD = 4 560 USD.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;\n	We came to the point when the balance of the PAMM account becomes 10 000 USD (Investor Cody 3 000 USD + Investor Milo 4 000 USD + Investor Hugo 3 000 USD). PAMM manager starts trading.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;\n	With an initial investment of 3 000 USD, Investor Hugo has gained a profit of 600 USD after the first month (30% of 2000 USD). Manager Leo is rewarded with the 30% performance fee of this amount: 180 USD. &lt;strong&gt;Investor Hugo&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; &lt;strong&gt;end balance after the first month is 3 000 USD + 420 (600-180) USD = 3 420 USD.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;\n	With an initial investment of 3 000 USD, &lt;strong&gt;Investor Cody&lt;/strong&gt; has also gained a profit of 600 USD after the first month (30% of 2 000 USD). Manager Leo - again - receives 180 USD to his commission a